content:
Hey all - I wanted to ask about a couple of old branches we have (I am a fan of pruning every so often :smile: )

https://github.com/HL7/genomics-reporting/tree/pa-refactor-CS-name
@Patrick Werner - Is this something we still need? I don't think so as I did some renaming as well, but take a look.

https://github.com/HL7/genomics-reporting/tree/krp
@Kevin Roberg-Perez - If I remember right, you took the JSON/XML examples and converted to FSH and back to JSON? Do we still need this branch? I suppose if we keep it, we need to delete from input/examples ?

As part of this cleanup, I am going to ask that Josh Mandel cleanup many of our old branch builds, which can be seen here:
http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/genomics-reporting/branches/

My rule will be that by next week, if the branch has been deleted in GitHub, I will ask that the branch build folder also be deleted. If that is a concern for anyone, please let me know.
Tagging a few folks that have some of the build branches:
@Bret H @Patrick Werner @May Terry @Kevin Roberg-Perez
I am not sure what https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/genomics-reporting/branches/BretOperationsExampleXMLpage/ branch is for anymore. Bob Dolin's work on Operations replaces it I believe.

Here are the published branches that I will propose deleting (will ask them to be deleted next Monday unless I hear differently):
